radiographic_examinations.findings: Left ventricular ejection fraction of 65%, normal left ventricular and right ventricular size and function, no significant valvular dysfunction.
No structural abnormalities or areas with late gadolinium enhancement; moderate narrowing of the mid left anterior descending and mid right coronary arteries.

99% tubular stenosis in the mid left anterior descending artery that improved to a 40% stenosis with intracoronary administration of nitroglycerin; another 40% mid left anterior descending artery stenosis and a 40% mid right coronary artery stenosis.
Depressed ejection fraction at 35% to 40% with global hypokinesis.
